# SPA build-time config (Vite) — COPY to `web/.env` and fill in.
# `.env*` is git-ignored. These are PUBLIC values baked into the bundle at build
# time (client ids / tenant id / scope are not secrets); never put an API key or
# client secret here — the browser would ship it.
#
# Leave ALL THREE unset for local dev: the SPA then runs unauthenticated (no
# sign-in gate, no Bearer token), pairing with the API's LOCAL_AUTH_BYPASS=1.
# Set all three to turn on Entra ID sign-in (MSAL) — against a dev-tenant app
# registration locally, or the real values injected by the SWA deploy workflow.

# SPA app-registration client id (Entra "Single-page application" platform,
# with a localhost redirect URI for dev, e.g. http://localhost:5173).
# VITE_AAD_CLIENT_ID=

# Entra tenant GUID (same tenant as the API app registration).
# VITE_AAD_TENANT_ID=

# The API's exposed scope — api://<AAD_API_CLIENT_ID>/access_as_user
# VITE_AAD_API_SCOPE=

# Optional — the API's base URL when it's a SEPARATE ORIGIN from the SPA (Azure:
# SWA calls the Function App hostname). Unset in local dev (Vite proxies /api).
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://<your-func-app>.azurewebsites.net
